<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="IntAreaBetween" checkit-title="Area between curves">
    <statement>
        <p>
Let <m>\mathbf{R}</m> be the finite region bounded by the graphs of
<m>y={\left(x - 5\right)}^{2} - 4</m> and <m>y=9 \, x - 49</m>.
        </p>

        <p>
Sketch an illustration of <m>\mathbf R</m>, and then
explain how to express the area of <m>\mathbf R</m> in the
following two ways:
        </p>

        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
As a definite integral with respect to <m>x</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
As a definite integral with respect to <m>y</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
(Do not evaluate either definite integral.)
        </p>
    </statement>

    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <me>
\int_{ 5 }^{ 14 } \left(-{\left(x - 5\right)}^{2} + 9 \, x - 45\right)dx
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <me>
\int_{ -4 }^{ 77 } \left(\frac{1}{9} \, y + \sqrt{y + 4} + \frac{4}{9}\right)dy
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
